      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "WASHINGTON, d. c., Dec. O.\nVIM. A. Herrin, Harriman's chief\npolitical leader on the Pacific coast\nand head of the Northern Pacific\nlaw department, has arrived in\nWashington to lead the fight\nagainst the lumbermen and the\ncongressional delegation Of the\nNorthwest who are backing Sen.\nFulton's bill against effective in\ncrease of rates until passed on by\nthe interstate commerce commits\nsion.\n\n\nThis afternoon congressman and\nsenators from the Northwest will\nmeet with delegates from the lum-\nDer companies and organize to\nfight for the bill."
    }
  ]
